description: Kelly Oubre Jr. knocked down two free throws with 7.7 seconds remaining in regulation to close out a 16-5 run and lift the Warriors over the Bucks, 122-121. Stephen Curry led the Warriors with 41 points, six rebounds and four assists, while Kelly Oubre Jr. finished the game with 19 points in the victory. Jrue Holiday (29 points, five assists) and Khris Middleton (28 points, seven assists) combined for 57 points for the Bucks in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 24-27 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 32-18.
